Police have arrested a 29-year-old man on suspicion of terrorism offences after a woman was stabbed outside a leisure centre on Thursday night. The incident occurred on Tommy Taylors Lane in Cheltenham, Gloucestershire Constabulary said. The woman was seriously injured, and was later taken to hospital for treatment. She remains in a stable condition. The attacker was arrested on suspicion of the commission, preparation or instigation of terrorism, as well as on suspicion of preparing acts of terrorism. The suspect was previously arrested on suspicion of attempted murder after the attack, but was then re-arrested on Friday under the Terrorism Act. He is being questioned by officers from Counter-Terrorism Policing and remains in detention. Assistant chief constable Richard Ocone, of Gloucestershire Constabulary, described the attack as an "isolated incident" He added: “I would like to reassure those living locally or visiting the county that we believe this was an isolated incident and we are not aware of any wider threat to members of the public,” he said. “We are working closely with our partners in Counter Terrorism Policing. “We appreciate that an incident of this nature may be concerning and we would encourage people to contact us via 101 with any additional information they may have about the incident.” More to follow...